Product name: BEST SELLING Vintage Nixie Clock - Art Deco design with Nixie tubes made in the Cold War Era - Wooden enclosure handcrafted by Nuvitron
Description:
༶ -- THE VINTAGE NIXIE TUBE CLOCK  -- ༶
With brand new, unused Nixie tubes that were rescued from exile in long abandoned basements in Eastern Europe, the Vintage Nixie Tube Clock imparts a warm glow from within its beautiful, handmade, Art Deco enclosure. Each clock casing takes over 30 hours to create and a lifetime to admire.
This Vintage Nixie Tube Clock is handcrafted using new old-stock tubes. These Nixie tubes are at least 30 years old, have never been used before and come from the former Soviet Union. Old school technology combined with an art deco style in a fine wooden handmade enclosure.
Bring to your home a piece of history with The Vintage Nixie Tube Clock and its Cold War era components.  The soft and warm glow of the Nixie tubes makes it perfect to use it in your bedroom. It won't disturb your sleep.
We guarantee the Vintage Nixie Tube Clock  to be free of material imperfections, and will replace for free any tubes that fail in the first two years after your purchase. Nixie tubes are known to last for decades, and ours operate in a range far below their peak, this ensures you will enjoy them for a long time.  
༶ -- FEATURES  -- ༶
༶ We extend the Nixies lifespan by turning on all the numbers evenly. You will see a random number effect each time a minute passes and a slot machine effect once each ten minutes.
༶ The brightness of your clock will start at a medium level. You can increase or decrease the brightness level if needed.
༶ Color LED´s behind the Nixie tubes will help you set the clock, the alarm and will have decorative effects that you can disable if desired.
༶ You can display time on 12 or 24 hours format as well as using the alarm mode to wake you up with a vintage style.
༶ The Vintage Nixie Tube Clock was designed to work below its operation point to ensure the tubes last longer. 
༶ Nixie tubes are neither soldered nor tightly fixed to the circuit board, but rather they can be easily swapable, provided that they’re held in place using copper pin connectors. In fact, our IN-12 Nixie Tubes are very common and easily available online.
༶ The clock can work flawlessly in the 5 continents because it accepts 110V and 220V in both frequencies, 50 and 60 Hz.
༶ -- RETRO TECHNOLOGY FROM THE COLD WAR ERA  -- ༶
Nixie tubes lie at the heart of our Nixie tube clocks and also give it them its name. The tubes were manufactured decades ago in the former Soviet Union, with the intention of being used in military equipment for purposes that are probably best left untold.
Each Nixie tube included in this clock contains 10 electrodes (one for each digit) made out of Molybdenum, and separated by ceramic rings. Everything is enclosed in a glass tube, filled with a mixture of Neon and Argon gases at low pressure. When a high voltage is applied, the electrodes in the shape of numbers glow in a warm orange color.
This tubes were kept in basements in their original boxes during the Cold War. For your enjoyment, Nuvitron brings this old school technology to your home, our Nixie tubes are new old stock never used before, and are at least 30 years old. 
༶ -- DESIGN AND CRAFTSMANSHIP  -- ༶
Our art deco enclosures are all handmade by skilled artisans and each one takes over 30 hours to create. There are no mass-produced, robot-made items here.
It has a handcrafted wooden enclosure made with selected woods such as Teak and Cedar to ensure a beautiful wood grain. The skilled artisans sanded by hand each piece and then glued them together to achieve a smooth surface guaranteeing there are not two identical Vintage Nixie Clocks.
We avoided lacquers and other artificial chemicals. Instead, we used natural oils that nourish the wood allowing it to breathe in any type of weather.
It has a curved lid made with thin sheets of wood and angular legs that gives an sculptural look. And to give the modern touch, we engraved our logo with laser.
༶ -- PRODUCT DIMENSIONS AND WEIGHT  -- ༶
7.8” width x 4.5” height x 3.8”depth
Weight is around one pound. 
༶ -- ELECTRICAL CHARACTERISTICS  -- ༶
Power consumption: 3W
AC Power Supply
Input: 100 - 240 Vac
          50/60Hz, 0.7A
Output: 12Vdc, 2A
༶ -- WHAT IS IN THE BOX?  -- ༶
༶ Nuvitron´s Vintage Nixie Tube Clock
༶ Power Adapter
༶ User's manual

Tape Length for Hoops: http://www.gnarhoops.com/#!tape-length-for-hoop/cr4f
------------ ☆ HOW TO ORDER ☆ ---------------
-- 1) SELECT: Tubing Selection & Recommendations --
1" PEX: Fabulous for the hooper that is down to chill with the hoop on his or her waist most of the time. Can be quite "heavy" for a hoop; the size and weight will limit ability to progress into the vast world of hoop tricks. Developmentally not recommended. Larger surface area makes tapes look stellar as ever and coils well, too. 37" and under in diameter is recommended.
3/4" PEX: Hands down best for beginners. The added few ounces mean worlds to the control and regulated speed offered by this tubing. Black in color, and a small bit flexy, this tubing coils like a breeze just like 5/8" Polypro but offers an experience comparable to 3/4" Polypro - transitioning just got real easy. 37" and under in diameter.
3/4" UV Polypro: Best for polypro beginners, more chill and controlled hooping, and a bit slower flow. Gnar digs the swag; slower sweeping pull-flows offer more controlled manipulations. Dampened response time, stellar for learning new tricks. 37" and under
 
5/8" UV Polypro: Light weight, responsive, gnarly all around. Fabulous for quick finger-tricks, doubles, minis, and a feather-light experience. May be considered bouncy at 32-34".
34" in diameter is your recommended max size to avoid wonk.
1/2" UV Polypro: Lighting fast, feather light, and ultra thin. No more than 30" OD, or else you may have a crazy noodle hoop. *Push Button unavailable for 1/2"
3/4" HDPE: Loved by beginners, and even craved by professionals. A bit more of a 'spring' to HDPEs responsiveness than Polypro, HDPE also offers about an ounce more weight for added control and decreased speed of tricks. Creamy, and semi-translucent white, naturally.
-- Your Taped Hoop --
Features: Push Button connection for collapsing, Full Taping of advertised tape in this listing

Includes: 1 Push Button, 2 Rivets, 1 Sandpaper, 2 UV Polypro Connectors, 30' Roll of Tape, Tubing

Description:
The Galaxy Hula Hoop pictured above is decorated with Galaxy Deco Duct tape, Purple Gaffer (grip) tape, and Black Gaffer (grip) tape in a spiral pattern.
Each Hula Hoop is handmade to order with lots of love and attention & can be made in a variety colors & sizes. This Galaxy Hula Hoop collapses to half its size (figure 8/ infinity style), for easy travel & storage. Each Hula Hoop is made with polyethylene tubing and is available in 2 tubing sizes, 3/4" 100 psi and 1/2" 125 psi. Your hula hoop will weigh between 1 and 2 lbs., depending on the size. This weight is ideal for fitness and exercise with your hoop, as well as for hoopdance.
CHOOSE YOUR COLORS
You can choose any color(s) to replace the purple and/or black gaffer tape for your own CUSTOM Galaxy Hoop!
Gaffer tape colors currently available:
Red. Burgundy. Teal. Electric Blue. Purple. Brown. Black. White.
Fluorescent Pink. Fluorescent Orange. Fluorescent Yellow. Fluorescent Green. *New!* Fluorescent Blue.
**Fluorescent gaffer tapes are UV reactive and glow under black light!*
CHOOSE YOUR SIZE
Extra Large: 41"-42" diameter (Beginner)
Large: 39"-40" diameter (Beginner)
Medium: 37"-38" diameter (Intermediate)
Small: 35"-36" diameter (Advanced)
Extra Small: 33"-34" diameter (Advanced/ Child)
XX Small: 32"-33" diameter (Advanced/ Child)      ~**~Size XX Small is available in 1/2" 125 PSI tubing only~**~
*Hoops can be made smaller than listed, but will not collapse. Please request a custom order for smaller, non-collapsible hoops*
CHOOSE YOUR TUBING
3/4" 100 PSI
- Standard hoop
- Perfect for beginners
- Great for exercise & dance
- Weighs between 1-2lbs
- Available in 34" diameter and up
1/2" 125 PSI
- Light weight
- Perfect for intermediate/advanced hoopers & children
- Great for dance, off body tricks, & isolations
- Available in 32" diameter and up
- Diameters larger than 38" not recommended
HOOP UPGRADES
Add a layer of crystal clear protective tape over the deco tape to help prevent damage & extend the life of your hoop!
Purchase your Upgrade here:   
https://www.etsy.com/listing/197474261/clear-protective-tape-upgrade-add-on-for
Please specify your desired colors and size at the time you place your hoop order. If no size is specified, your hoop will be made 40" in diameter. If no colors are specified, your hoop will be made with purple gaffer tape and black gaffer tape as pictured in the product display photos. 
To determine a good size for your hoop, measure the distance between the floor and your bellybutton. 40 in. diameter is often recommended for beginner hoopers. The larger and heavier the hoop, the easier it is to keep around the body. So if you were never able to hoop as a kid, a bigger hoop may be just what you need to get started!
The Galaxy Collapsible Hula Hoop will make a *SteLLaR* new addition to any hooper's (always growing) collection!

Product name: Original Claddagh Ring Sterling Silver
Description:
The Claddagh ring (Irish: fáinne Chladaigh) is a traditional Irish ring given which represents love, loyalty, and friendship (the hands represent friendship, the heart represents love, and the crown represents loyalty).
The design and customs associated with it originated in the Irish fishing village of Claddagh, located just outside the old city walls of Galway, now part of Galway City. The ring, as currently known, was first produced in the 17th century.
The Claddagh ring belongs to a group of European finger rings called "fede rings". The name "fede" derives from the Italian phrase mani in fede ("hands [joined] in faith" or "hands [joined] in loyalty"). These rings date from Roman times, when the gesture of clasped hands was a symbol of pledging vows, and they were used as engagement/wedding rings in medieval and Renaissance Europe.
Fede rings are distinctive in that the bezel is cut or cast to form two clasped hands that symbolize faith and trust or "plighted troth". The Claddagh ring is a variation on the fede ring, while the hands, heart, and crown motif was used in England in the early 18th century.
Towards the end of the 20th century there was an explosion of interest in the Claddagh Ring, both as jewelry and as an icon of Irish identity. In recent years it has been embellished with interlace designs and combined with other Celtic and Irish symbols, but this is a very recent phenomenon that corresponds with the worldwide expansion in popularity of the Claddagh ring as an emblem of Irish identity.

Easyweed is our best-selling heat transfer vinyl due to its semi-adhesive clear carrier that allows you to weed small vinyl letters and fine designs easily. Much thinner than other heat transfer vinyl materials, EasyWeed offers excellent durability, even after repeated washings. Quick Info
Compatible Fabrics:
100% cotton
100% polyester
Cotton/polyester blends
Leather
Washing/Aftercare Instructions:
Machine wash inside-out warm with mild detergent
Dry at normal setting
Do not use chlorine bleach
Do not dry clean
Pressing Instructions
Cut design in reverse and weed away outside vinyl material, leaving only your transfer on the clear liner.
Preheat garment at 305F for about 2-3 seconds.
Press vinyl transfer to garment at 305F for 10-15 seconds using medium/firm pressure.
If layering: Transfer first layers with just 2-5 second press time. Press final color layer for 10 secs.
Peel the clear liner away while the transfer is warm.
